Uses of Package
com.fluidops.iwb.mapping

Packages that use com.fluidops.iwb.mapping
com.fluidops.iwb.mapping Simple mapping framework. 
com.fluidops.iwb.provider provider for harvesting data from external datasources and for accessing services (that also cause side effects such as starting a VM) 
com.fluidops.iwb.util utility classes for SSL support, process handling, strings, etc. 
 

Classes in com.fluidops.iwb.mapping used by com.fluidops.iwb.mapping
AlignmentOperator
          interface that helps providers to either generate owl:sameAs or align URIs before entering data into the triplestore the API is inspired by the SILK Link specification language: http://www4.wiwiss.fu-berlin.de/bizer/silk/spec/ It usually defines 2 datasources: source: the IWB repository target: the provider graph passed on as a List of Statements LinkCondition: currently simplified to a Pair of predicate URIs.
Data
          base class for all mapping data models such as tree, table, graph, pojos, etc.
GraphData
          simple graph data model. does not know about RDF data model yet.
PojoData
          pojo datamodel.
RdfData
          RDF data model.
StringData
          raw string data
TableData
          table datamodel. delegates to com.fluidops.iwb.provider.TableProvider.Table
TableData.PropertyType
          Column types for the underlying table, used when translating to RDF
TreeData
          XML Tree data model
